\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In today's video, I present the changes to the Overlord. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Up until now, the Overlord could be used very effectively as an early scouting unit without requiring much attention. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition, the Creep Generation ability was rarely used, as the speed bonus on creep provided too little of an advantage, especially when the generated creep area was relatively small. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Since Zerg also lack units that can move across cliffs, they rely more heavily on flying transport units than other races. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Therefore, the Overlord now generates creep over a larger area, and creep increases the health regeneration of Zerg ground units instead of their movement speed. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Since the speed bonus mainly benefited melee units, the Overlord previously had to fly directly over enemy forces, or at least get very close, to spread creep in a way that actually supported them. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
With the new changes to creep, however, it's now valuable to spread creep under ranged units as well, allowing them to survive longer. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This means the Overlord can position itself above or even behind its own army, rather than being within easy firing range of the enemy. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
As a result, the opponent faces an interesting choice \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c push forward to kill the Overlords and reduce the healing effect... or continue focusing on the rest of the Zerg army. <break time="1.0s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To give Zerg also more mobility starting from the early game, Ventral Sacs now requires the Evolution Chamber instead of the Lair. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This means it's no longer enough to block narrow ramps to keep the Zerg out of your own base \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c players must secure larger areas instead! <break time="0.4s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition, the Overlord's movement and turning speed have been reduced to reinforce the immersion that the Overlord is a rather slow creature and cannot instantly turn 180 degrees.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f}
