\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In this video, I'll be introducing the changes to the Hydralisk. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In the original StarCraft II, the Hydralisk is a glass cannon \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c a fragile unit that, due to its higher tech level, naturally comes with a higher cost. <break time="0.4s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The question at the time was \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c which attribute could Blizzard enhance to justify the Hydralisk's tech level and cost? <break time="1.0s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The Zergling had already taken the role of high mobility, and the Roach filled the role of strong armor, which didn't leave much else. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
So the answer seemed clear \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c the Hydralisk had to deal a lot of damage, since it couldn't take much in return. <break time="1.0s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
So it was clear that the Hydralisk had to deal a lot of damage since it couldn't take much itself. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Blizzard also wanted every Tier 1.5 unit to feel completely new, to make StarCraft II stand apart from StarCraft 1 and strike a balance between familiar and fresh gameplay \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c at least, that's my interpretation and my claim. <break time="1.0s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Unfortunately, this focus underestimated the importance of gameplay depth and sacrificed too much of it just to make StarCraft II feel newer and more innovative. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
As a result, the Roach became a Tier 1.5 unit, a cheap, tanky unit that would actually make far more sense as a Tier 2 unit. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Tanky units usually shouldn't be available in large numbers, because they can easily become too strong, especially when they're ranged units. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To avoid too much overlap with the Zergling, Blizzard made the Roach from a melee unit to a ranged unit. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To also avoid too much overlap with the Hydralisk, Blizzard made the Roach unable to attack air units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
After all, you need hard counters against mass-producible tanky units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
And since we're talking about Zerg, it would also feel strange if the Tier 1.5 unit couldn't be produced in large numbers. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The idea behind the Roach wasn't bad \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c it works reasonably well, but I believe it has much more potential as a Tier 2 unit. <break time="0.4s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Moving it up would also open the door for the Zerg to have an early-game anti-air unit that's actually effective at moving out of the base and taking the fight to the opponent. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The Hydralisk would be perfect for that role, but because StarCraft II needed to look and feel "new and different," gameplay quality suffered as a result. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
And we all know how much Zerg struggles in professional matches when they're forced to play defensively until the late game. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Thankfully, I have different priorities. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
So in sc2YouWant, I've swapped the roles of the Hydralisk and the Roach, making the Hydralisk a Tier 1.5 unit. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This gives Zerg players an early anti-air option that also works well offensively and creates more strategic possibilities. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Meanwhile, the Roach can now fully realize its potential as a Tier 2 unit \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c it can be more expensive, tankier, and come with strong abilities like Burrow Movement right from the start. <break time="0.4s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The design challenges and solutions around Burrow Movement will be discussed in the Roach video. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
As a Tier 1.5 unit, the Hydralisk is now cheaper, deals less damage, and has many upgrades that keep it relevant later in the game. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
It counters Zerglings and Banelings less harshly than the Roach did, but still performs well against them, especially with increasing levels of micro skill. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The new defensive tools available to Zerg also make it easier to counter Zerglings and Banelings even without relying on the Hydralisk. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
For example, Creep Tumors can now spawn two Broodlings, workers can enter the main building to deploy Broodlings, and the Spine Crawler's size has been increased to help block enemy units more effectively. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
One could argue that Zerg intentionally don't have an early anti-air unit capable of moving out offensively, in order to emphasize the differences between the races. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
But in my opinion, the price you pay for that in terms of gameplay and strategic diversity is too high.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
