\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
090_Swarm Host}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In this video, I'll be introducing the changes to the Swarm Host. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The Swarm Host has long become just a harassment unit that you rarely see anymore. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition, Locusts block the movement of enemy units and prevent them from reaching the unit that spawned them. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The same is true for Broodlings, and even there it's already quite strong, but at least Broodlings are melee units and have less life, which means that in large numbers they usually deal less effective damage because of limited space, and more importantly, they are much easier to kill. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
And because Locusts and Broodlings cannot attack air units, they are even more similiar. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
That's why in sc2YouWant, Locusts are now always flying and never land and they can attack both ground and air units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This gives ground armies a better chance to counter the Swarm Host, while still forcing them to pay attention to positioning and avoid the flying waves of Locusts whenever possible. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Additionally, Locusts spawn much faster, live longer, and move fast when near Swarm Hosts. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To balance this out, Locusts have less health, deal less damage, and move very slowly when they are too far away from Swarm Hosts. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition, the Swarm Host costs slightly fewer minerals but significantly more vespen gas. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This design means Zerg players have to defend their Swarm Hosts more carefully, but they can also do so effectively using the Locusts. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Zerg now gain an additional anti-air option that works well both defensively and offensively, an additional siege option, an additional harassment option, an additional base defense option and can also be a part of the main army. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Locusts live long enough and spawn quickly enough that each Swarm Host can maintain up to six active Locusts to defend or attack. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This forces opponents to rely on anti-air splash damage or long-range units to deal with Swarm Hosts. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Beyond all these new strategic and tactical options, the Zerg now feel even swarmier thanks to this new version of the Swarm Host. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Because Swarm Hosts must burrow to spawn Locusts, and Locusts only move quickly near Swarm Hosts, the unit also becomes more counterable. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To make the Locusts feel even more swarm-like, their wings no longer flap in sync \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c each one moves individually, making them look more like a living swarm of insects and less like a group of robots.\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
