\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
120_Infestor}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f\u9552\'3f}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In this video, I present the changes made to the Infestor. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In the original Starcraft 2 the Infestor has the abilities Fungal Growth, which slows enemies and deals damage over time; Microbial Shroud, which reduces incoming damage from air and ranged units within a targeted area; and Neural Parasite, which temporarily takes control of an enemy unit while the Infestor must remain close to it. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Fungal Growth has the weakness that its projectile is very difficult to dodge and it slows too heavily, leaving little room for reaction. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
However, players generally want to be able to react to things as much as possible, so I want to change Fungal Growth as follows. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Fungal Growth now reduces the armor and shield armor of affected ground units instead of slowing and damaging air and ground units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Additionally, if a unit affected by Fungal Growth dies while under its effect, it spawns two Broodlings. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This change makes it easier to respond to the new Fungal Growth through healing and other defensive abilities, especially after being hit by it. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Once units are affected, players will want to keep those specific units alive rather than the unaffected units, since their deaths would otherwise spawn additional enemy units that deal damage. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Microbial Shroud has been changed and moved to the Viper. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In return, the Infestor now has Parasitic Bomb, allowing for an effective answer to mass air units earlier in the game. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
More details regarding the changes to Microbial Shroud will be covered in the video about the Viper changes. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
The energy cost and damage against non-armored units of Parasitic Bomb have been slightly reduced, while its range, duration, and damage against armored units have been increased. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Since Neural Parasite is also a high-risk, high-reward ability that is mainly effective only against expensive late-game units, I wanted to replace it with a new ability that is more useful across all stages of the game and against a wider range of units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Therefore, Neural Parasite has been removed and replaced with Plague Cloud. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Plague Cloud continuously deals low damage to ground units over a large area for a long period of time. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
It can be used as a damage boost in long engagements, such as breaking or preventing sieges. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition, Plague Cloud can serve as a harassment tool, since it doesn't deal its full damage instantly but over time, forcing the affected player to periodically pull workers away from resources to heal, repair, or recharge shields. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
As a result, players will want to avoid being hit by Plague Cloud at all costs \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c which means keeping Infestors at a distance. <break time="1.0s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition to its new abilities, all of the Infestor's existing abilities can now be used while burrowed, greatly increasing its versatility. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
However, the Infestor now moves much more slowly when burrowed. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Like all burrowed units, it takes 50% less damage and receives a brief speed boost upon unburrowing, allowing it to retreat more easily. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This updated set of Infestor abilities enables many new strategies, and each ability now has the potential to be seen more frequently, especially since all of them can now be cast while burrowed. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition, the mechanical and visual design of its abilities now align more closely with its latest concept art from before Wings of Liberty was released.}
