\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In this video, I present the changes to the Nydus Network and Nydus Worm. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Nydus Worms can transport an unlimited number of units across the map in a very short time. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This ability is extremely powerful \uc2 \u8212\'81\'5c in my opinion, too powerful. <break time="0.4s" />\uc1 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This is also one of the reasons why usually only a single Nydus Worm is needed, which feels less "Zerg-like." <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
In addition, the creep spread of the Nydus Worm is so large that it's harder to spawn it in a hidden location. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
Because of this, a single moment of inattention from the opponent can make the Nydus Worm so powerful that it often ends the game. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To make individual Nydus Worms easier to counter, each Nydus Worm can now only spawn 16 units before going on cooldown, after which it can spawn another 16 units. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To encourage using multiple, more hidden Nydus Worms, the Nydus Network cost and the Nydus Worm's creep spread have been reduced. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
At the same time, the cost of the Nydus Worm has been slightly increased to make every failed use of the Nydus Worm more punishing. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
To ensure that Zerg players can still easily move their armies between their bases, Nydus Networks can still spawn an unlimited number of units without cooldown. <break time="1.0s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This makes it easier to build multiple Nydus Networks and to use several Nydus Worms simultaneously. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
This feels more "Zerg-like," while at the same time a single Nydus Worm can no longer unload unlimited units continuously, making multiple Nydus Worms necessary when using them in a more obvious and aggressive manner. <break time="0.4s" />}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10\loch
However, if you pursue a longer-term strategy where the Nydus Worms are meant to remain undetected, a single Nydus Worm can still be sufficient, since its reduced creep spread makes it harder to spot.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\rtlch\af11\afs24\alang1081 \ltrch\lang1031\langfe2052\hich\af3\loch\ql\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\ltrpar\cf0\f3\fs24\lang1031\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\fi0\li0\lin0\ri0\rin0{\rtlch\afs28 \ltrch\hich\af6\loch\cs17\rtlch\af12 \ltrch\hich\af5\loch\f5\dbch\af7\fs28\f6\dbch\af10
\~}
